				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Aggro Management<a name="45912"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 2:05 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span> I got a question related to aggro management. I have a 16 bard, twinked a little bit, nothing major. I've also played a Beastlord to 30's and a druid to 55 in the kunark days. I haven't played alot since, just returned to EQ. 
<br />

<br />
 I was in a PC group, mostly DPS, no cleric, super twinked warrior, and I was just getting decimated by aggro. The only time I could keep the aggro off of me was if I never meleed and only stood back and twisted heal and anthem. If I did melee I would only play anthem, and I would end up grabbing aggro pretty quick.
<br />

<br />
   A ranger in the group said I was getting level based aggro since I was only 16 and the rest were 20ish. Is this the case or is a Bard just a super aggro class. I like playing the bard, it has alot more depth than a BST or Druid, but the learning curve is steep. I logged out a bit frustrated, since I felt a bit useless just standing there twisting songs.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
