			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Aggro Management<a name="45917"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 14 04 2:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>First of all, twisting hym with a lute is what probably kept your group going without much downtime! Useless pah! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Aggro in the lower levels is funky and in no way correlates to what you'll see later on. The only reason your getting it up the butt is because A) bandits comes in bunches B) Your playing a heal song which causes a small amount of aggro C) the adds are not being bashed or angered by anyone else but your songs, they only have proxie aggro on the warrior which is negligable hate, a pulse of hymn will more than likely pull them to you.
<br />

<br />
You mentioned you were lvl 16, a song became available to you at lvl 15 called Kelin's Lucid Lullaby. It is a single target mesmerization song. It lasts 18 seconds so you can easily lock down 3 or 4 mobs. Next time you find yourself in this situation, step back and mezz the adds instead of playing heal or fighting, Make sure the group understands that you are mezzing and to assist the MA/Puller. This way you limit risk to yourself AND keep damage to your group at a minimum.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
