				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Aggro Management<a name="46155"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 15 04 1:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've just started playing a twinked out warrior.  He is lvl 21 and fighting in PC too.  Before my warrior was 20, I noticed that the aggro from bards, rangers, and others was more than I could taunt off.
<br />

<br />
When my warrior made lvl 20, he got his first incite tome.  This ability allows a warrior to to generate 400 units of instant hate and continues to build hate much the way a dot works.  When I went back to PC with this new ability, I was able to grab aggro from anyone in my group and keep it.  
<br />

<br />
I would suggest you just keep playing the way you do and somewhere in your 20s, the warriors will be able to keep aggro.</span></td>
