				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Aggro Management<a name="46161"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 15 04 1:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>all good suggestions, I just want to echo Shilbah's in particular, making sure you're not &quot;buffing&quot; the group at the moment the mob arrives is a key way to avoid agro at all levels. 
<br />

<br />
This is actually true for anyone casting a buff just as the mob gets to camp (before MT has fully established agro)  but since bards are constantly &quot;buffing&quot; every 6 seconds or so, they tend to see agro from it the most. It can get ugly on raids at higher levels where you are playing AE mana or resists.  
<br />

<br />
I remember one particular moment in North ToV when about 4 flurry drakes arrived in camp just as the enchanter's MGB KEI landed.  Oops dead chanter :P</span></td>
