				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, if the uber warrior didn't get his new hate disc, then I must say (having played two melees past the 20s) is that taunt sucks at that level. You have real problems keeping aggro as a lowbie warrior. You just mash taunt hoping to get it up in skill for later. You rely on your damage to get and keep aggro.
<br />

<br />
That being said, early on, bards are pretty kick A$$ on melee so it's not suprising that you stole aggro, especially if you're twisting songs that benefit the group like healing damage monsters cause...
<br />

<br />
Don't worry, you need the aggro occasionally to work up your ever ellusive defense skill.  Other than that, you will find later on that you can't hold aggro if you want to, so enjoy it (or not) while you can, hehe.
<br />

