				<td colspan="2"><span>Definately stick with the bard... The lower levels are good, but the full power of the bard becomes apparent with a larger repertoire.  You will be able to amaze your friends with single pulls in LDoN and confound them with swarm kiting.  You will soon be capable of unique combinations of simultaneous group wide buffs, targetted or AoE debuffs and so on.  Read the guides section for the full salivatory possibilities.
<br />

<br />
After Paludal (you're prolly already out of there <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />) try sol A, off LavaStorm (take the Neriak book).  After you ding 30 in there you will see a message which tells you to try ToFS.  I have a feeling that there is a progression of zones with an agreeable XP bonus, which you can follow for a streamlined career into the planes.  It's when you're at this level that you will see the true power of the bard - the frustration will be worth it.</span></td>
